  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Season chicken with smoked paprika, cumin, garlic powder, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Heat coconut oil in a skillet over medium-high heat and sear the chicken for 2-3 minutes per side.",
    "Transfer chicken to a baking sheet and bake for 12-15 minutes or until cooked through.",
    "Meanwhile, crumble tempeh into small pieces and pan-fry until crispy.",
    "Mix together pico de gallo sauce, sriracha, and rice vinegar in a bowl.",
    "To assemble the bowls, place cooked chicken and crispy tempeh on a bed of greens, drizzle with pico de gallo sauce, and garnish with fresh cilantro.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
